svg.text: This model illustrates the implementation of a simulation program developed in the Dymola modeling environment for Modelica. The Modelica model has been exported as a Functional Mock-up Unit (FMU) for co-simulation. The FMU computes the temperature change in two rooms with different capacity. Input to the FMU are the control signal u_k. Output of the FMU are the new room temperatures T_{k+1}. The control action is computed in Ptolemy II.
Output simulation time and wall clock time. This is for illustration purposes only and not needed by the above model.
